quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,11,"Say, \"I have been commanded to worship God, dedicating my faith to Him"
  39,12,"And I have been commanded to be the first [among you] to submit"
  39,13,"Say,\" I fear the punishment of a terrible Day should I disobey my Lord"
  39,14,"Say, \"God [alone] do I worship, sincere to Him in my faith"
  39,15,"so worship what you will besides Him.\" Say, \"Truly doomed are the ones who will lose themselves and their families on the Day of Resurrection. Truly, that is a self-evident loss"
  39,16,"They will have curtains of fire above them and below them. With this God puts fear into His worshipers. So be ever mindful of Me, My worshipers"
  39,17,"Those who have avoided the worship of false deities and turned toward God will have good news, so give good news to My worshipers"
  39,18,"who listen to what is said and follow what is best. Those are the ones God has guided, and those are the people endowed with insight"
  39,19,"As for one who deserved the decree of punishment, can you [Prophet] save one who is already in the Fire"
  39,20,"But those who are mindful of their Lord, for them are dwellings built one above the other, beneath which rivers flow. [This is] God's promise and God does not fail to deliver [His] promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that God sends down rain from the sky and guides it through the earth to flow as springs? Then with it He produces vegetation of varying colors, which later withers, and you see it turning yellow, then He turns it into waste. That is a reminder for those endowed with insight"